Object-Oriented Programming
1st Set-First Exercise

Manual:
	To compile this program write to terminal
the command "make". To delete the executable and
the object files write the command "make clean".

To execute the program the command line must have the
following form:

./Train_Simulator <number of stations> <number of waggons>

where these two parameters are integers. Moreover, the 
program prints the money that the train collected from
fines and from legal passengers. And prints for each
waggon how many passengers have escaped checking and how
many illegal passengers were caught.
